<TITLE> Hasina meets with top civil servants </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 11 (bdnews24.com)  Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has sat with secretaries to all ministries and divisions of the government on Sunday. "There is a convention of holding meetings with secretaries of different ministries and divisions immediately after the new prime minister takes office," cabinet secretary MA Aziz tells bdnews24.com. "The prime minister will give the top civil servants directives on different issues including usual work plans and fast implementation of ADP projects." The new head of government will herself be briefed on the state of things from the secretaries, the cabinet secretary added. bdnews24.com chief reporter Ehsanul Haque Babu reports that the prime minister was sitting with ministers and state ministers at the Secretariat from around 10:40 am Sunday. She is set to hold a meeting straight after with the secretaries to the ministries and divisions for the first time since she took office for her second term as PM. bdnews24.
